   "source": [
    "### Beispiel: One Feature is not enough\n",
    "\n",
    "<div>\n",
    "    <img src=\"attachment:5b308ee9-48eb-40fa-9918-a9f1966ff148.png\" width=300>\n",
    "</div>\n",
    "\n",
    "In einem vergangenen Beispiel haben wir zwei Klassen anhand __eines__ Features mittels Hypothesentests unterschieden. Oft kann man durch die Extraktion weiterer Features die _Klassifizierbarkeit_ von Daten verbessern. Daher untersuchen wir in diesem Beispiel vorliegende Zeitserien anhand mehr als einem Feature und visualisieren uns die Daten im Feature-Raum mittels Scatter-Plots."
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "import scipy.stats\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Sample 1\n",
    "distribution1 = scipy.stats.gengamma(20, 20, loc=50, scale=45)\n",
    "sample1 = distribution1.rvs(size=10000)\n",
    "plt.hist(sample1, bins=100)\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "print(distribution1.stats('mvsk'))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Sample 2\n",
    "distribution2 = scipy.stats.gengamma(1, 50, loc=50, scale=20)\n",
    "sample2 = distribution2.rvs(size=10000)\n",
    "plt.hist(sample2, bins=100)\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "print(distribution2.stats('mvsk'))\n",
    "\n",
    "sample1 = sample1 - sample1.mean()\n",
    "sample2 = sample2 - sample2.mean()\n",
    "sample1 = sample1.reshape(sample1.shape[0], 1)\n",
    "sample2 = sample2.reshape(sample2.shape[0], 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "samples = np.concatenate((sample1, sample2), axis=1)"
   ]

   "source": [
    "# Load\n",
    "samples = np.load('./data/data_more_features.npy')\n",
    "\n",
    "# To pandas\n",
    "df = pd.DataFrame(samples)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Rolling\n",
    "window_size = 800\n",
    "\n",
    "# First trial\n",
    "#name_feature1 = 'mean'\n",
    "#name_feature2 = 'kurt'\n",
    "\n",
    "# Second trial\n",
    "#name_feature1 = 'std'\n",
    "#name_feature2 = 'kurt'\n",
    "\n",
    "# Third trial\n",
    "name_feature1 = 'std'\n",
    "name_feature2 = 'skew'\n",
    "\n",
    "df_feature1 = df.rolling(window_size).agg(name_feature1)\n",
    "df_feature2 = df.rolling(window_size).agg(name_feature2)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Look at dists\n",
    "plt.figure()\n",
    "sns.distplot(df_feature1.iloc[:, 0])\n",
    "sns.distplot(df_feature1.iloc[:, 1])\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure()\n",
    "sns.distplot(df_feature2.iloc[:, 0])\n",
    "sns.distplot(df_feature2.iloc[:, 1])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Concatenate for visualization\n",
    "df1 = pd.concat([df_feature1.iloc[:, 0], df_feature2.iloc[:, 0]], axis=1)\n",
    "df1.columns = [name_feature1, name_feature2]\n",
    "df1['label'] = 1\n",
    "df2 = pd.concat([df_feature1.iloc[:, 1], df_feature2.iloc[:, 1]], axis=1)\n",
    "df2.columns = [name_feature1, name_feature2]\n",
    "df2['label'] = 2\n",
    "df = pd.concat([df1, df2], axis=0)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Scatter plot\n",
    "plt.figure()\n",
    "sns.scatterplot(data=df, x=name_feature1, y=name_feature2, hue='label', palette='jet');"
   ]

    "### Beispiel: Embedding Digits\n",
    "\n",
    "<div>\n",
    "    <img src=attachment:294c36cd-8d63-42fc-a8d6-fba03961a451.png width=150>\n",
    "</div>\n",
    "\n",
    "In `sklearn` gibt es ein bekanntes Dataset - `load_digits()`. In ihm liegen uns handgeschriebene Zahlen vor. Jede Zahl wird ursprünglich durch ein Array der Dimension `(8, 8)` repräsentiert. Im Datensatz liegen die Zahlen als Zeilenvektoren in einer großen Datenmatrix vor. Wir wollen uns in diesem Beispiel diesen 64-dimensionalen Datensatz in den zweidimensionalen Raum mittels `TSNE` projizieren."
   ]

   "source": [
    "# Import\n",
    "from sklearn.datasets import load_digits\n",
    "from sklearn.manifold import TSNE\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load digits data\n",
    "X, y = load_digits(return_X_y=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Show digits\n",
    "plt.imshow(X[0, :].reshape((8, 8)))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fit t-SNE to data\n",
    "tsne = TSNE()\n",
    "X_embedded = tsne.fit_transform(X)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Compare shape\n",
    "print(X.shape)\n",
    "print(X_embedded.shape)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot low-dimensional data\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))\n",
    "sns.scatterplot(X_embedded[:, 0], X_embedded[:, 1], hue=y, legend='full', palette='jet')"
   ]

   "source": [
    "### Beispiel: Massive Feature Extraction from Time Series using TSFRESH\n",
    "\n",
    "<div>\n",
    "    <img src=\"attachment:d46d1d81-cb7a-403d-a32e-6eb3ec10b0aa.png\" width=200>\n",
    "</div>\n",
    "\n",
    "_Quelle: https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/datasets/Robot+Execution+Failures_\n",
    "\n",
    "Um uns den Workflow einer massiven Feature-Extraktion zu verdeutlichen, nutzen wir den Datensatz \"Robot Failures\" des UCI Machine Learning Repositories. Dieser ist in TSFRESH direkt hinterlegt. \n",
    "\n",
    "_\"This dataset contains force and torque measurements on a robot after failure detection. [...] Each robot records time series from __six different__ sensors. Each feature represents a force or a torque measured after failure detection; each failure instance is characterized in terms of 15 force/torque samples collected at regular time intervals starting immediately after failure detection; The total observation window for each failure instance was of 315 ms.\"_\n",
    "\n",
    "Wir wenden in diesem Beispiel die `extract_features` Funktion an, um eine Feature-Matrix aus Zeitseriendaten zu generieren. Die `impute` Funktion, um die Feature-Matrix für die weitere Verarbeitung vorzubereiten, und die `select_features` Funktion, um hypothesentestbasiert den Feature-Raum zu verringern. Einen Teil des reduzierten Feature-Raumes lassen wir uns dann mittels des t-SNE Verfahrens visualisieren."
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "## Feature Selection"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {
    "c5933c06-1c93-43e7-b858-2cd97b9a3c54.png": {
     "image/png": ""
    }
   },
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Beispiel: Correlation-based Selector\n",
    "\n",
    "<div>\n",
    "    <img src=\"attachment:c5933c06-1c93-43e7-b858-2cd97b9a3c54.png\" width=150>\n",
    "</div>\n",
    "\n",
    "In diesem Beispiel schreiben wir uns eine Funktion, die uns aus einer Feature Matrix mit der Shape `(num_samples, num_features)` die `num_features` Features auswählt, die am höchsten mit dem Target bzw. Label korrelieren. Wir wollen das sowohl mit einem Loop, als auch mit der Berechnung einer Korrelationsmatrix lösen."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Generate Data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 25,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Import\n",
    "from sklearn.datasets import make_regression\n",
    "\n",
    "# Generate data\n",
    "X, y = make_regression(n_samples=200, n_features=7, n_informative=4)\n",
    "data = np.concatenate((X, y.reshape(-1, 1)), axis=1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 104,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Save\n",
    "np.save('./data/corr_selector_features.npy', X)\n",
    "np.save('./data/corr_selector_target.npy', y)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Lösung"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 105,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Load\n",
    "X = np.load('./data/corr_selector_features.npy')\n",
    "y = np.load('./data/corr_selector_target.npy')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 106,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def corr_selector_loop(X, y, num_features):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    corr_array = np.zeros(shape=(X.shape[1]))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # calculate the correlation with y for each feature\n",
    "    for index, feature in enumerate(X.T):\n",
    "        corr_array[index] = np.corrcoef(feature, y)[0, 1]\n",
    "        \n",
    "    # Feature selection\n",
    "    sorted_corr_array = np.sort(corr_array)\n",
    "    is_selected = (corr_array >= sorted_corr_array[-num_features])\n",
    "    return X[:, is_selected]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 107,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(200, 5)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 107,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "X_sel = corr_selector_loop(X, y, 5)\n",
    "X_sel.shape"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 108,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.image.AxesImage at 0x1b148e0ac70>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 108,

     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {

    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Calculate and show correlation matrix\n",
    "data = np.concatenate((X, y.reshape(-1, 1)), axis=1)\n",
    "plt.imshow(np.corrcoef(data.T))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 109,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def corr_selector_mat(X, y, num_features):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    # Calculate correlation matrix\n",
    "    data = np.concatenate((X, y.reshape(-1, 1)), axis=1)\n",
    "    corr_mat = np.corrcoef(data.T)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Feature selection\n",
    "    corr_array = corr_mat[:-1, -1]\n",
    "    sorted_corr_array = np.sort(corr_array)\n",
    "    is_selected = (corr_array >= sorted_corr_array[-num_features])\n",
    "    return X[:, is_selected]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 110,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [

      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 110,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "X_sel = corr_selector_mat(X, y, 5)\n",
    "X_sel.shape"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "### Beispiel: Recursive Feature Elimination\n",
    "\n",
    "<div>\n",
    "    <img src=\"attachment:a0690c52-4cc2-4c6f-a860-f3b1a075de8c.png\" width=150>\n",
    "</div>\n",
    "\n",
    "In diesem Beispiel laden wir uns das Digits-Dataset und führen eine Recursive Feature Elimination durch. Wir nutzen hierfür eine Support Vector Machine als Klassifikator.\n",
    "Wir werden sehen, dass vor allem die Randbereiche der Bilder für die Klassifikation eine untergeordnete Rolle spielen."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Lösung"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 114,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.svm import SVC\n",
    "from sklearn.datasets import load_digits\n",
    "from sklearn.feature_selection import RFE\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load the digits dataset\n",
    "digits = load_digits()\n",
    "X = digits.images.reshape((len(digits.images), -1))\n",
    "y = digits.target\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create the RFE object and rank each pixel\n",
